        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 17 at 5:03PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 503 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking an area of strong
thunderstorms extending from 7 miles west of Custer to 15 miles
northeast of Hardin moving south at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Custer and Crow Indian Reservation.

This statement does not include the city of Billings.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
